	<header class="article-header">
		<div class="article-context">Facts So Romantic <span class="article-tag">On
				<a href="/term/l/Biology"><span class="article-tag">Biology</span></a></span></div>

		<h1 class="article-title">These Medical Terms Still Bear the Mark of the Third Reich</h1>
					<p class="byline">Posted By Sarah Zhang on Sep 28, 2016</p>
		
		


<section class="social-tools">
    <ul>


        <li><a href="#comm" class="jump-to-comments"><i class="icon-comments"></i> Add a comment </a></li>

        <li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?s=100&p%5Bsite_name%5D=Nautilus&p%5Btype%5D=website&p%5Burl%5D=http%3A%2F%2Fnautil.us%2Fblog%2Fthese-medical-terms-still-bear-the-mark-of-the-third-reich&p%5Btitle%5D=These+Medical+Terms+Still+Bear+the+Mark+of+the+Third+Reich+-+Facts+So+Romantic+-+Nautilus&p%5Bsummary%5D=Dr.+Hans+Reiter+achieved+the+one+thing+most+likely+to+keep+a+physician%E2%80%99s+name+in+textbooks+forever%3A+He+got+an+illness+named+after%26%238230%3B&p%5Bimages%5D%5B0%5D=http%3A%2F%2Fstatic.nautil.us%2F1248_39e4973ba3321b80f37d9b55f63ed8b8.jpg" target="_blank"  class="fb-share obnd_lnk" data-trval="these-medical-terms-still-bear-the-mark-of-the-third-reich" data-trlbl="facebook" data-tract="social_share"><i class="icon-facebook"></i> Facebook</a></li>
